						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vatatīrthanātha temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 25: 932 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that three <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land at Andavanallūr, which Araiyaṉ Vīrachōḷaṉ obtained (as tenant-cultivator) gave it up in favour of the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Andavanallūr.</p>						

						<p>Note: The individual Araiyaṉ Vīrachōḻan obtained the right to cultivate the land as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīkka</hi> (unextinguishable tenant) from the king himself and the land dues assigned to the temple was reduced to 310 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> from 360 <hi rend="italic">kalam.</hi> He in his turn, had conveyed his rights of inextinguishable tenancy to the <hi rend="italic">ūrār.</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. VIII No. 669. </p>						

						</summary>
